article.headline: Belmont 79, Marshall 74
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Scott Saunders scored 23 points and Belmont defeated Marshall 79-74 on Thursday night. Saunders was 8 of 16 from the field and a perfect 7-for-7 from the free-throw line for the Bruins, who made their few 3-pointers at an opportune time. Belmont (9-5) was just 4 of 12 from long range, but went 3 of 3 during a key stretch. Tied at 14 with 8:15 left in the first half, Kerron Johnson and Trevor Noack made back-to-back 3's to spark a 13-1 Bruins' run. J.J. Man's 3-pointer capped the spurt with 5:14 to play. Johnson finished with 16 points for Belmont, which improved to 6-0 at home this season. De'Andre Kane led the Thundering Herd (9-3) with 25 points. Damier Pitts and Robert Goff added 14 points apiece for Marshall, which snapped a four-game winning streak. Marshall had won the previous meeting between the two schools, 87-86, on Dec. 19.
